            "answer_text": "They are pretty much synonyms. What libertarians debate is how small government should be an how do we get rid of as much taxation as possible. Obviously, those in government don\u2019t like to hear such debates. it\u2019s about the size and scope of powers. The more powers (scope of influence) we grant the government the larger it has to be. When it starts curtaining competition and productivity is when problems arise. Where is the balance? ",
